mad_libs.before:
LICE'S UPSIDE-DOWN WORLD
Lewis Carroll's classic, "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland", as well
as its sticky sequel, "Through the Looking sun",
have enchanted both the young and old walnutss for the last
101 years, Alice's chubby adventures begin
when she runs down a/an bitter hole and lands
in a strange and topsy-turvy army. There she discovers she
can become a tall banana or a small jellyfish simply by
nibbling on alternate sides of a magic violin. In her travels
through Wonderland, Alice kickeds such remarkable
characters as the White milk, the grumpy Hatter,
the Cheshire jigsaw, and even the Queen of Zeuss.
Unfortunately, Alice's adventures come to a/an abundant
end when Alice awakens from her Zeus.
